Lightning Message Service (LMS) : - It enables you to to communicate between Two Independent component without any relation.
     Before implementing LMS we have some prerequisites:- 
                          1). Create a MessageChannel :- 
                                    a). Need a development environmnet like vs code or some editor
                                    b). Navigate to: force-app/main/default/   
                                    c). Create a folder named messageChannels (if not exist) name is case-sensitive.
                                    d). Create a new file inside that folder
                                    e). File Name like ChannelName.messageChannel-meta.xml
                                                            Example: sampleSadiqChannel.messageChannel-meta.xml
                                    f). copy the metadata code from browser and paste and make the neccessary changes like exposed true, name.
                                    g). deployed the file to the org.
                              
                        channel metadata code:- 
                                                    <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
                                                    <LightningMessageChannel xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
                                                    	<masterLabel>sampleSadiqChannel</masterLabel>
                                                    	<isExposed>true</isExposed>
                                                    	<description>This is channel is used to carry the data for two independent component.</description>	
                                                    </LightningMessageChannel>

                     Message channel got created, import it by adding __c in the channel name in the lwc.
                    eg: - import SAMPLEMC from "@salesforce/messageChannel/sampleSadiqChannel__c"
          *****************************************************************************************************************
     
Now create a Two LWC component As I have created in my org with the below Names: - 
                    1). p_2026_LMS_A_Component
                    2). p_2026_LMS_B_Component

          Code of p_2026_LMS_A_Component: - 
                                        JS: - 
                                   ----------------
                                             import { LightningElement, wire } from 'lwc';
                                             import SAMPLEMC from "@salesforce/messageChannel/sampleSadiqChannel__c"
                                             import {MessageContext, publish} from 'lightning/messageService'
                                             export default class P_2026_LMS_A_Component extends LightningElement {
                                                 inputValue
                                             
                                                 @wire(MessageContext)
                                                 context
                                             
                                                 inputHandler(event){
                                                     this.inputValue = event.target.value
                                                 }
                                             
                                                 publishMessage(){
                                                     const message={
                                                         lmsData:{
                                                             value:this.inputValue,
                                                             FullName: 'Sadique Alam',
                                                             RollNumber : '1234'
                                                         }
                                                     }
                                                     //publish(messageContext, messageChannel, message)
                                                     publish(this.context, SAMPLEMC, message)
                                                 }
                                             }
                                        Html
                                   ---------------
                                        <template>
                                            <lightning-card title="LWC to LWC Communication LMS Component A">
                                                <div class="slds-m-around_medium">
                                                    <lightning-input type="text" label="Enter message to publish" 
                                                    onkeyup={inputHandler}></lightning-input>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="slds-m-around_medium">
                                                    <lightning-button label="Publish" onclick={publishMessage}></lightning-button>
                                                </div>
                                            </lightning-card>
                                        </template>

          Code of P_2026_LMS_B_Component: - 
                                        JS: - 
                                   ----------------
                                                  import { LightningElement, wire } from 'lwc';
                                                  import SAMPLEMC from "@salesforce/messageChannel/sampleSadiqChannel__c"
                                                  import {subscribe, MessageContext, APPLICATION_SCOPE, unsubscribe} from 'lightning/messageService';
                                                  export default class P_2026_LMS_B_Component extends LightningElement {
                                                      recievedMessage
                                                      subscription
                                                      @wire(MessageContext)
                                                      context
                                                  
                                                      connectedCallback(){
                                                          this.subscribeMessage()
                                                      }
                                                  
                                                      subscribeMessage(){
                                                          //subscribe(messageContext, messageChannel, listener, subscriberOptions)
                                                          this.subscription= subscribe(this.context, SAMPLEMC, (message)=>{this.handleMessage(message)}, {scope:APPLICATION_SCOPE})
                                                      }
                                                  
                                                      handleMessage(message){
                                                          this.recievedMessage = message.lmsData.value? message.lmsData.value :'NO Message published'
                                                          window.alert('Hardcoded value came: - ',message.lmsData.FullName);
                                                          console.log('Hardcoded value came: - ',message.lmsData.FullName);
                                                      }
                                                  
                                                      unsubscribeMessage(){
                                                          unsubscribe(this.subscription)
                                                          this.subscription = null
                                                      }
                                                      
                                                  }
                                        Html
                                   ---------------
                                                  <template>
                                                      <lightning-card title="LWC to LWC Communication LMS LMS Component B">
                                                          <div class="slds-m-around_medium">
                                                             <lightning-button label="unsubscribe" onclick={unsubscribeMessage}></lightning-button>
                                                          </div>
                                                          <div class="slds-m-around_medium">
                                                              Message Recieved <strong>{recievedMessage}</strong>
                                                          </div>
                                                  
                                                      </lightning-card>
                                                  </template>
               *******************************code end *************************************************************

     Below are the things has been provided by the 'lightning/messageService' library: - 

                    1). MessageContext: - It connects component to the LMS using the @wire service.
                              syntax: -  @wire(MessageContext)
                                             context
                    2). publish: - It Send's the data packet to the message channel.
                              syntax: -   publish(this.context, ImportedMessageChannel, PublishingData)
                    3). subscribe: - It recieve the data packet from the message channel through MessageContext.
                              syntax: - this.subscription = subscribe(this.context, ImportedMessageChannel, (message)=>{this.customMethodCalling(message)}, {scope:APPLICATION_SCOPE})

                    4). unsubscribe: - It unsubscribe the channel, so it stop the listener immediatily.
                              syntax: - unsubscribe(this.subscription), this.subscription is subscription object.

                    5). createMessageContext: - It is the manual way to establish a connection to the Lightning Message Service.
                    6). releaseMessageContext: - It is the manual way to remove a connection to the Lightning Message Service.

     APPLICATION_SCOPE : - you are telling the LMS Engine to ignore the tab boundary.

